title: [Western Waterway, Charl's Teeth]
description: Sharp, glossy obsidian reflects the moon's light off the Teeth, illuminating where a few shards have fallen into the water and now litter the sandy floor.  Daring the strong current, an anchored boat of gnomish design rocks back and forth precariously in the churning water.
paths: Obvious paths: north, northeast, east, southeast, south
